  "summary": {
    "intent": "Migrate the web UI from vanilla JavaScript with HTM tagged templates to TypeScript with JSX/Preact components, then incrementally improve type safety with enums, typed RPC, typed WebSocket events, and reduced DOM casts.",
    "outcome": "Full migration completed: 135 JS files converted to 142 TypeScript/TSX files with Vite build pipeline, 0 tsc errors, 0 `as any`, typed RPC registry (107 methods), typed WebSocket events (28 enum members), ChannelType enum, and DOM casts reduced from 443 to ~134. local-validate passes clean.",
    "learnings": {
      "repo": [
        "The project uses `include_dir!` to embed `crates/web/src/assets/dist/` into the Rust binary at compile time — `dist/` must be committed so `cargo build` works without Node.js",
        "Source maps in dist/ add 27MB to the embedded binary; Vite sourcemaps should be disabled in the build config (`build.sourcemap: false`)",
        "The codebase uses a `registerPage` + imperative DOM pattern where pages are not full Preact component trees — JSX components are rendered into a container element but the page body uses `querySelector`/`getElementById` extensively",
        "HTM tagged templates (`html\\`...\\``) were opaque to both TypeScript and Biome — switching to JSX exposed ~89 `noNonNullAssertion` and a11y violations (useButtonType, noLabelWithoutControl) that existed in the original code but were invisible",
